      <hedline>
        <hl1>Corrections</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Correction of June 3 front-page article on Labor Department's employment report for May</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>A front-page article on Saturday about the Labor Department's employment report for May misstated the period for a forecast of economic growth made by Macroeconomic Advisers, a consulting firm in St. Louis. In predicting growth closer to 3 percent than to the 4.5 percent originally forecast, it referred to the second half of the year, not the second quarter.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
